<br />
<br />
Shaman gain upgraded CHeals (same as druids, but behind clerics)<br />
Shaman gain supernal remedy (same as druids, but behind clerics)<br />
Shaman gain rez spells (same as druids, but behind clerics)<br />
Shaman gain some sort of mitigation/regen pet thing<br />
Shaman lose Tnarg's mending and Daluda's Mending<br />
<br />
Druids get upgraded CHeals (same as shamans, but behind clerics)<br />
Druids get rez spells (same as shamans, but behind clerics)<br />
druids gain supernal remedy (same as shamans, but behind clerics)<br />
Druids get a brand new line of HoT spells (slightly better than clerics, vastly better than shamans)<br />
Druids lose Nature's Infusion and Sylvan Infusion<br />
<br />
Clerics get better stackability on Virtue<br />
Clerics no longer pay reagent costs on Virtue<br />
Clerics lose symbol line<br />
<br />
I'm not convinced that the "remedy" line is sufficient fast healing to leave the three priest classes balanced.  Clerics I group with in places like Tipt seem to use either CHeals or "light".  Rarely do they use rememy.  This proposal as written would dramatically reduce the fast healing power of a level 65 druid and somewhat reduce it for a shaman also I think.  Would have to do the math to be sure.</div>
