			<!-- icon and title -->
			<div class="smallfont">
				
				<strong>Epilogue, Common Priest Utility and Defense</strong>
			</div>
			<hr size="1" style="color:" />
			<!-- / icon and title -->
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div><b>Variant DA for all priests</b> <br />
Realizing that with stronger healing will come increased healing aggro, and knowing from experience the strong shortcomings of bo DA and DB (Divine Aura and Barrier), I propose all priests get the following self-buff:<br />
<br />
Spiritual Armor of Protection<br />
Cler/Dru/Sha, self only<br />
Effects:<br />
1. Drain 200 mana per tick<br />
2. Restore 100 hit points per tick<br />
3. Reduce hate towards caster by 200 per tick<br />
4. Increase resists by +300<br />
5. 1000pt damage aborbing rune, refreshed each turn<br />
6. Movement speed reduced to 0<br />
7. Unable to engage in melee attacks at all<br />
8. All spell gems greyed out.<br />
<br />
Benefit here for everyone, but especially any cleric left behind when an evac happened while DA was up, is that while you cannot heal yourself, others can heal you, duration is not fixed, but harshly limited by available mana, the very large improvements to resists and mitigation-via-rune are designed to allow priests to "survive occasional aggro" at a very high mana cost if it sustains long without permanently enhancing their tanking abilities or otherwise infringing on the role of the tank archetype classes in groups.<br />
<br />
<i>Others</i><br />
All common "caster" spells would be shared among priests: invis, levitate, etc., single target and the upgraded versions as well.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
