	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>I'm not overly familiar with the druid line of spells, so please corrent me if I'm wrong. <br />
<br />
In your list, you're saying that druids would have no "viable" fast casting direct heal in the end game, instead their healing would all be replaced by HoTs that are the most efficient in the game. <br />
<br />
I cannot speak for other clerics in this, but that seems reasonable to me. Except, I know I would not want to be without some means of fast and direct healing. While not having an overall spell line in that, I think the idea would be alot better if druids got at least 1. Make it less mana efficient, so it's not a worthwhile spell to cast all the time, but good in an emergency. I could see alot of problems stemming from druids not being able to heal fast enough when the shite hits the fan.<br />
