		<div>Aean, go back and reread.  In groups, the two most often used spells in pickup groups not on the cutting edge, post 60 anyway, are cheal and supernal remedy.  Supernal Light doesn't really get useful without HA3/HG3 and some nice spell haste anyway.  The point here was to give druids and shamans real healing upgrades that would be enough at a minimum to "get by" as a healer in a group, and be a meaningful raid healer as well, while also attempting to preserve some diversity and keeping at least a bit of cleric superiority in methods if not power.  Druids gain one thing here they have been screaming for for a while, a spell at level 63 that heals a base of 1.5khp in just a second or two casting time, affected by HG/HA, and a cheal that is likewise worth casting, and also affected by both.<br />
<br />
Sounds like a win for them without making them "just as good" as clerics.  Its not quite the full balancing of power I would want, but it seemed a good start for compromise and discussion.</div>
