<br />
Haste: /wave 2 other classes that can haste and one that can overhaste with the right song.<br />
<br />
CC: Only 2 classes of 16 can universally CC, 2 others have situational CC vs. undead and summoned respectively, and in the latter case its a level 65 PoP spell.  I've watched groups fail to form for a lack of it when, being non-raiders and not having gear that makes it pointless, CC becomes vital.<br />
<br />
Cleric Nukes: Eliminate knockback, recast delay, elimate resists and have it do damage like HoTG (averaging 1/2-2/3 max) PLUS automatic criticals vs. undead PLUS bonus damage versus undead PLUS a summoned hammer pet that is commandable and persistent and scaled up in power to match a shamans PLUS having its own bonus damage vs. undead and a HoTG proc of its own.  This is insufficient DPS improvements?<br />
<br />
Clerics have: Widest range of healing spells, rez to 96%, the Light line, and a clickable rez from the epic.<br />
<br />
All Priests have: A fast-cast "rescue heal", a slow cast "cheal", and various low-aggro HoT spells, rez to 90%<br />
<br />
All priests get better buff stacking<br />
<br />
All priests get more focused damage dealing abilities that are easier to measure and benchmark against other classes (because there are fewer variables) so they can (barring unusual circumstances) stay at or around a desired benchmark of DPH compared to pure mana-based DPS.<br />
<br />
Oh, and Damage Shields?  You're kidding right?  Unless they were changed to be a percentage-based DS off the damage dealt by the mob, or enhanced in some other rather serious way, DSes take a buff slot (premium in some cases) and provide only marginal real benefit to group total damage dealt, especially in the high end.</div>
